cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AR 

This paper involves the implementation of machine learning techniques for optimizing and quantizing chromatic dispersion filters in digital backpropagation, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of deep learning also suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the optimization and implementation of hardware components may fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
